Subject: drm/amd/display: Add null check for 'afb' in
 amdgpu_dm_plane_handle_cursor_update (v2)
Git-commit: cd9e9e0852d501f169aa3bb34e4b413d2eb48c37
Alt-commit: 0fe20258b4989b9112b5e9470df33a0939403fd4
Patch-mainline: v6.12-rc1
References: jsc#PED-9898 jsc#PED-10191 jsc#PED-10197 jsc#PED-10226 jsc#PED-10237 jsc#PED-10340 jsc#PED-10852 jsc#PED-11022 bsc#1232335 CVE-2024-49908 bsc#1232357 CVE-2024-49905

This commit adds a null check for the 'afb' variable in the
amdgpu_dm_plane_handle_cursor_update function. Previously, 'afb' was
assumed to be null, but was used later in the code without a null check.
This could potentially lead to a null pointer dereference.

Changes since v1:
- Moved the null check for 'afb' to the line where 'afb' is used. (Alex)

Fixes the below:
drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/../display/amdgpu_dm/amdgpu_dm_plane.c:1298 amdgpu_dm_plane_handle_cursor_update() error: we previously assumed 'afb' could be null (see line 1252)

